The present XML file has been created by Giuseppe G. A. Celano, 6 March 2015, at Leipzig University.
The following text comes from The Homeric Hymns and Homerica with an English Translation by Hugh G. Evelyn-White. Homeric Hymns. Cambridge, MA.,Harvard University Press; London, William Heinemann Ltd. 1914.
The original file containing the text comes from PerseusDL:
https://github.com/PerseusDL/canonical/blob/master/CTS_XML_TEI/perseus/greekLit/tlg0013/tlg002/tlg0013.tlg002.perseus-grc1.xml
The text has been automatically checked for Unicode codepoints, so that it only contains the correct Greek letters from the Unicode Chart Greek Extended and Unicode Chart Greek and Coptic (for example, no mathematical Greek letters).
I have automatically checked punctuation: all colons (U+003A) are middle dots (U+00B7) and all apostrophes (U+0027) are modifier letter apostrophes (U+02BC).
